<subSubSection id="6DC56513FFCEFFC2E292A6B5CD3E71CB" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="25603698FFCEFFC2E292A6B5CA507087" blockId="32.[151,1436,1234,1477]" box="[151,1040,1234,1261]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFCEFFC2E292A6B5CF727086" bold="true" box="[151,306,1234,1261]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">
<typeStatus id="FA64883AFFCEFFC2E292A6B5CE927087" box="[151,210,1235,1261]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFCEFFC2E33CA6B5CCA77087" authority="Scudder, 1885" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1885" box="[313,743,1234,1261]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Tribochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFCEFFC2E33CA6B5CC7D7087" box="[313,573,1235,1261]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Tribochrysa inaequalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="414E4B69FFCEFFC2E046A6B5CCA77087" author="Scudder, S. H." box="[579,743,1234,1261]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" pagination="721 - 831" refId="ref25635" refString="Scudder, S. H. (1885) Systematische Ubersicht der fossilen Myriopoden, Arachnoideen und Insekten. In: Zittel, K. A., Handbuch der Palaeontologie. Abt. 1. Palaeozoologie. Bd 2. Mollusca und Arthropoda. Verlag von R. Oldenbourg, Munchen, Leipzig, pp. 721 - 831. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 2492" type="book chapter" year="1885">Scudder, 1885</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by subsequent monotypy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25603698FFCEFFC2E2C2A691CF4C7117" blockId="32.[151,1436,1234,1477]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFCEFFC2E2C2A691CFF6717A" bold="true" box="[199,438,1270,1297]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Emended diagnosis.</emphasis>
The venation is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFCEFFC2E13FA691CD94717B" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1882" box="[826,980,1271,1297]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Palaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFCEFFC2E13FA691CD94717B" box="[826,980,1271,1297]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Palaeochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but may be distinguished from it by the fore- and hind wing Psm strongly zigzagged [
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFCEFFC2E099A77DCD76715F" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1882" box="[668,822,1307,1333]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Palaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFCEFFC2E099A77DCD76715F" box="[668,822,1307,1333]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Palaeochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: nearly straight, very slightly zigzagged], Psm formed only by two-three branches of RP [
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFCEFFC2E029A759CC867133" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1882" box="[556,710,1343,1369]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Palaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFCEFFC2E029A759CC867133" box="[556,710,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Palaeochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: five branches], and RP with eight branches [
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFCEFFC2E6D0A759CB2F7133" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1882" box="[1237,1391,1343,1369]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Palaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFCEFFC2E6D0A759CB2F7133" box="[1237,1391,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Palaeochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 13 branches].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25603698FFCEFFC2E2C2A7E0CD3E71CB" blockId="32.[151,1436,1234,1477]" box="[199,894,1414,1441]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFCEFFC2E2C2A7E0CFD371CA" bold="true" box="[199,403,1414,1440]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Species included.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFCEFFC2E39FA7E1CC6A71CB" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1885" box="[410,554,1415,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Tribochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFCEFFC2E39FA7E1CC6A71CB" box="[410,554,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">T. inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFCEFFC2E064A7E1CD3971CB" authority="Scudder, 1890" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1890" box="[609,889,1415,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Tribochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="firmata">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFCEFFC2E064A7E1CC8E71CB" box="[609,718,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">T. firmata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="414E4B69FFCEFFC2E0D3A7E1CD3971CB" author="Scudder, S. H." box="[726,889,1415,1441]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" pagination="1 - 734" refId="ref25710" refString="Scudder, S. H. (1890) The Tertiary insects of North America. Report of the United States Geological Survey of the Territories, 13, 1 - 734, 28 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 44698" type="journal article" year="1890">Scudder, 1890</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
